Text.Value: Because her throne rests on lies, more than a hundred gish scholars could count in a lifetime. I will share but two.
Child of Gith. I've not come to kill you. I've come to aid you.

Text.Value: If they have not said, they must have good reason. And I won't be the one to betray them.

Text.Value: Be at ease. I bring only truth.

Text.Value: I'm not giving you the Astral Prism, if that's what you're wanting.

Text.Value: Your blade speaks for you, kith'rak. You've come for blood.
I served Vlaakith the whole of my life. Learned her words, fought her battles, yet she names me Hshar'lak. Your words carry truth.

Text.Value: I know you carry the Astral Prism, Lae'zel.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quietly but with rising determination and consideration

Text.Value: The zaith'isk does not purify - it extracts memory and kills the infected. Nor does the lich queen glorify the ascended. She feeds on most all of them to grow her power and pursue godhood.

EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to Lae'zel.

Text.Value: Vlaakith is my queen. Why would I want to end her?
Your doubt does not make it any less true, child.
Speak. My ear is yours.
Don't trust him.
Don't trust him.
Bring the Prism to Baldur's Gate. I'll be waiting in a taproom called Sharess' Caress. That is where we decide the fate of our people.
Bring the Prism to Baldur's Gate. I'll be waiting in a taproom called Sharess' Caress. That is where we decide the fate of my people.
All that remains is the key that unchains them - and I've found someone who I believe can provide it.
Now - to Baldur's Gate. I'll be waiting, Lae'zel.
Your cronies tried to kill us. Why should Lae'zel listen to you?

Text.Value: No. I don't believe it.

Text.Value: I've not come to kill you, Lae'zel. I've come to aid you.

The queen's warriors hunt you. The qua'nith will sound out when you come near their portals. Hear its cry, and prepare for battle - or slip away.
I've sought their freedom for aeons. When the Prism went missing, I feared the worst.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel breathes in sharply, cloises her eyes, lowers her blade, and calms herself. Finally, she has seen through her Queen's lies.

EditorData.NodeContext: Thoughtful, not too vehement.

Text.Value: Lies, Lae'zel - every last one. There is no purification, no ascension.

Kill him. This is your chance to earn Vlaakith's redemption.

Who is the person inside the Prism?

Synopsis: Voss arrives at camp and attempts to sway Laezel to his side after the events of the Creche. The Avatar can push Laezel to either agree or stay true to herself, potentially putting her on her Orpheus path.
